OL,4,Chigh on cocaine has sentence increased
OL,6,FAfter he and two friends were kicked
OL,7,Fout of the last pub they had drank in,
OL,8,FWhiteman drove at "highly
OL,9,Finappropriate speeds for a built-up
OL,10,Farea or village". Mr Brocklehurst
OL,11,Fadded they had reached speeds said to
OL,12,Fbe up to 60mph where the limit was
OL,13,F20mph.
OL,15,FMr Brocklehurst said Whiteman, who
OL,16,Frefused to have his blood taken after
OL,17,Fthe incident, struck Kaylan as he
OL,18,F"stood in a place where you would
OL,19,Fexpect to be safe" on the pavement,
OL,20,Fwith his friends watching on.
